rmk:
Voice at 0:00, weaker one at 0:16, stronger one at 0:26.
Two black kites followed this intruder (these kites were seen
through trees) and expelled it.  It is rare to meet a grey-faced buzzard
here other than in the season of migration.
High-frequency (around 8 kHz) notes were probably from
a fledgling of Ficedula narcissina.

rmk:
Recorded by an unattended recorder.  I saw two flying birds
15 min later, and they were most likely the source of this voice.
This species does not usually live in this region and these
individuals may have been juveniles in dispersal.
Insect sound and distant traffic noise overlapped (not modified).
The interval between two phrases was shortened to show them
on the sonogram.  The actual interval was 11s.
